243
00:08:26,898 --> 00:08:29,498
We're not acting arrogant. We know how you must feel now.

244
00:08:31,068 --> 00:08:33,238
- We're just being sympathetic.
- This is...

245
00:08:34,538 --> 00:08:36,538
(Unable to say anything)

246
00:08:37,178 --> 00:08:39,507
- Giants' fans feel small now.
- Right.

247
00:08:39,508 --> 00:08:42,777
- Which team do you support?
- I don't support a specific team.

248
00:08:42,778 --> 00:08:44,518
I see. Then you stay quiet today.

249
00:08:45,918 --> 00:08:47,618
- What about you, Jae Suk?
- Doosan Bears.

250
00:08:47,658 --> 00:08:49,587
- Doosan Bears.
- I support Doosan Bears.

251
00:08:49,588 --> 00:08:51,758
- Last year must've been a hard one.
- My gosh.

252
00:08:51,988 --> 00:08:54,027
- But the thing is...
- You know what?

253
00:08:54,028 --> 00:08:55,097
They can come back from it.

254
00:08:55,098 --> 00:08:56,867
(They can come back from it.)

255
00:08:56,868 --> 00:08:58,127
- The thing is...
- I'm rooting for your team too.

256
00:08:58,128 --> 00:08:59,928
You know what? Hear me out.

257
00:09:00,138 --> 00:09:03,337
I'm so happy to see Giants and Eagles doing well.

258
00:09:03,338 --> 00:09:06,267
- I hope Giants have a great year.
- Yes. I'll do our best.

259
00:09:06,268 --> 00:09:07,637
I'm not the one playing, though.

260
00:09:07,638 --> 00:09:10,007
- It's not something you can affect.
- Seriously.

261
00:09:10,008 --> 00:09:12,378
- No. I mean I can root for them.
- You can root for them.

262
00:09:12,578 --> 00:09:13,648
Come on, it's the Giants!

263
00:09:13,678 --> 00:09:15,418
(Laughing)

264
00:09:16,118 --> 00:09:17,488
(Feeling sad within minutes)

265
00:09:17,818 --> 00:09:19,018
Are you guys the competitive type?

266
00:09:19,148 --> 00:09:20,457
In Sung, would you say you're competitive?

267
00:09:20,458 --> 00:09:21,817
I used to be, but now...

268
00:09:21,818 --> 00:09:23,527
- You're not competitive anymore?
- when I have to compete...

269
00:09:23,528 --> 00:09:24,788
for something,

270
00:09:25,328 --> 00:09:28,257
I'd say, "Let's say you won." I just withdraw from competing.

271
00:09:28,258 --> 00:09:30,297
- You're not motivated to compete.
- Yes.

272
00:09:30,298 --> 00:09:32,298
I'm not really good at games now.

273
00:09:32,628 --> 00:09:35,368
You're in a slump now, right? I have the yips now.

274
00:09:35,998 --> 00:09:38,037
(Yips: The state where players can't perform easy skills due to anxiety)

275
00:09:38,038 --> 00:09:39,908
- Don't exaggerate now.
- I have the yips now.

276
00:09:40,278 --> 00:09:41,378
Are you good at games, Hae Joon?

277
00:09:41,708 --> 00:09:43,408
Not really.

278
00:09:44,208 --> 00:09:45,847
- Well...
- Who will win the presents today?

279
00:09:45,848 --> 00:09:47,177
- You know what?
- Right, I'm worried about that.

280
00:09:47,178 --> 00:09:48,778
- But I try hard once I play.
- Okay.

281
00:09:49,048 --> 00:09:51,088
- What about you, Jeong Min?
- I'm the fiery type.

282
00:09:51,448 --> 00:09:52,987
- You're fiercely competitive?
- Really?

283
00:09:52,988 --> 00:09:55,218
- That's great.
- You're the fiery type?

284
00:09:55,418 --> 00:09:56,928
- Are you really?
- I'll show you later.

285
00:09:57,028 --> 00:09:58,758
- Today...
- Are you that good?

286
00:09:58,958 --> 00:10:01,297
It always doesn't match what they say. At some point,

287
00:10:01,298 --> 00:10:03,597
Hae Joon will be screaming like this. "Let's go!"

288
00:10:03,598 --> 00:10:05,128
- I see.
- I think...

289
00:10:05,468 --> 00:10:06,838
Will there be kids on the show today?

290
00:10:07,638 --> 00:10:09,238
- You can't tell us.
- They won't tell us.

291
00:10:09,398 --> 00:10:10,967
We can never seem to succeed...

292
00:10:10,968 --> 00:10:12,537
when we are invited to elementary schools.

293
00:10:12,538 --> 00:10:13,807
Last week, we went to an elementary school...

294
00:10:13,808 --> 00:10:15,038
after a long time, but we failed again.

295
00:10:15,078 --> 00:10:17,707
There's that sense of pressure and anxiety...

296
00:10:17,708 --> 00:10:20,007
- that we can't fail.
- Right.

297
00:10:20,008 --> 00:10:22,148
We won't be going there since the kids are on a break now.

298
00:10:22,248 --> 00:10:23,547
- We went there last week.
- Really?

299
00:10:23,548 --> 00:10:26,217
We met a school sports team.

300
00:10:26,218 --> 00:10:27,858
Hae Joon, you don't seem to pay attention.

301
00:10:29,258 --> 00:10:30,387
(Chuckling)

302
00:10:30,388 --> 00:10:31,887
Well, you know I was thinking...

303
00:10:31,888 --> 00:10:34,598
- Hae Joon definitely loves himself.
- Right.

304
00:10:34,798 --> 00:10:36,398
- During our time in Latvia, - Yes.

305
00:10:36,828 --> 00:10:38,497
he kept showing us the music video he starred in...

306
00:10:38,498 --> 00:10:40,128
- when he was young.
- He showed it to you?

307
00:10:40,668 --> 00:10:42,668
It was "Move" by Yoon Sang.

308
00:10:43,368 --> 00:10:44,837
- Really?
- If you haven't watched it,

309
00:10:44,838 --> 00:10:46,268
watch it.

310
00:10:48,138 --> 00:10:50,107
(The music video recommended by Hae Joon,)

311
00:10:50,108 --> 00:10:52,048
(featuring him when he was young and handsome)

312
00:10:52,778 --> 00:10:54,348
(Feeling proud)

313
00:10:54,718 --> 00:10:56,178
- Shall we get going?
- Yes.

314
00:10:57,348 --> 00:10:58,517
(Amazed)

315
00:10:58,518 --> 00:10:59,948
- They're the places we'll visit.
- What's that?

316
00:11:00,118 --> 00:11:01,518
"Kim Sin Woong."

317
00:11:01,718 --> 00:11:02,857
- Sin Woong?
- Yes.

318
00:11:02,858 --> 00:11:04,927
"I cut, tap, and make holes."

319
00:11:04,928 --> 00:11:07,227
- "I'm an owner with a beard..."
- Is he a carpenter?

320
00:11:07,228 --> 00:11:08,827
- "who works with knives,"
- I think he is.

321
00:11:08,828 --> 00:11:10,598
"awls, chisels, and hammers."

322
00:11:10,828 --> 00:11:12,997
"On the outside, I may look somewhat rough."

323
00:11:12,998 --> 00:11:14,598
"But I have the biggest heart."

324
00:11:14,668 --> 00:11:17,767
- "Visit Gangdong Community Lounge."
- "Community Lounge?"

325
00:11:17,768 --> 00:11:18,807
It sounds like he might be a carpenter...

326
00:11:18,808 --> 00:11:20,877
- A carpenter.
- or work with tools.

327
00:11:20,878 --> 00:11:21,878
A carpentry workshop.

328
00:11:21,879 --> 00:11:23,908
We can take the bus there.

329
00:11:24,178 --> 00:11:25,307
I'll look it up.

330
00:11:25,308 --> 00:11:26,308
It's been a long time since I last rode the bus.

331
00:11:26,309 --> 00:11:27,317
I sometimes take the subway.

332
00:11:27,318 --> 00:11:29,848
- Really?
- The bus routes changed a lot.

333
00:11:30,248 --> 00:11:31,817
It takes 20-something minutes.

334
00:11:31,818 --> 00:11:34,118
- Let's get going.
- We should head out now.

335
00:11:34,858 --> 00:11:35,918
Let's go.

336
00:11:36,558 --> 00:11:37,687
- Jeong Min. The bus is coming.
- Yes.

337
00:11:37,688 --> 00:11:38,828
- We must hurry.
- Okay.

338
00:11:40,128 --> 00:11:41,827
It's a bit iffy.

339
00:11:41,828 --> 00:11:43,027
- Why?
- If we walk,

340
00:11:43,028 --> 00:11:44,668
- It will take two minutes?
- we might miss it.

341
00:11:45,668 --> 00:11:46,767
We must rush then.

342
00:11:46,768 --> 00:11:47,837
- Or...
- It's two minutes away?

343
00:11:47,838 --> 00:11:48,868
(The bus will arrive at the stop shortly.)

344
00:11:48,968 --> 00:11:50,138
Isn't that the bus?

345
00:11:50,608 --> 00:11:51,608
Wait. Is that it?

346
00:11:51,609 --> 00:11:52,637
- No. It's not that one.
- No. We have to...

347
00:11:52,638 --> 00:11:53,707
- take the bus on the other side.
- On the other side.

348
00:11:53,708 --> 00:11:54,738
We have to take it on the other side?

349
00:11:54,838 --> 00:11:56,177
(Walking in a hurry)

350
00:11:56,178 --> 00:11:58,107
- My gosh. This place...
- It's over there.

351
00:11:58,108 --> 00:11:59,307
- Where?
- There goes the bus.

352
00:11:59,308 --> 00:12:00,417
- It's that bus!
- That one?

353
00:12:00,418 --> 00:12:01,717
- Where?
- Hold on. No.

354
00:12:01,718 --> 00:12:04,418
- It's that bus.
- We can't cross now.

355
00:12:04,618 --> 00:12:05,787
- Sir!
- The next one will come...

356
00:12:05,788 --> 00:12:06,817
in 14 minutes.

357
00:12:06,818 --> 00:12:08,058
- In 14 minutes?
- No.

358
00:12:08,218 --> 00:12:09,688
- It's over there.
- My gosh.

359
00:12:09,788 --> 00:12:11,927
(They quickly signal to the bus,)

360
00:12:11,928 --> 00:12:13,427
(but the bus departs without them.)

361
00:12:13,428 --> 00:12:14,628
My gosh. That was the bus.

362
00:12:15,528 --> 00:12:16,827
Then we have to wait...

363
00:12:16,828 --> 00:12:17,927
- for ten minutes outside.
- Oh, no.

364
00:12:17,928 --> 00:12:20,028
- Ten minutes?
- We should've taken our time then.

365
00:12:20,098 --> 00:12:21,638
Had we known, we would've taken our time.

366
00:12:21,898 --> 00:12:23,138
Look. Did the bus leave?

367
00:12:23,438 --> 00:12:24,508
- It must be down the street.
- Right.

368
00:12:24,568 --> 00:12:26,237
- Over there.
- It stopped there.

369
00:12:26,238 --> 00:12:27,338
Yes.

370
00:12:27,608 --> 00:12:29,038
My gosh. What a bummer.

371
00:12:30,038 --> 00:12:31,308
We should go to the bus stop.

372
00:12:31,548 --> 00:12:32,807
Let's grab a taxi over there.

373
00:12:32,808 --> 00:12:34,518
(Let's grab a taxi over there.)

374
00:12:36,148 --> 00:12:37,748
- He grew up comfortably.
- I knew it. Right.

375
00:12:39,348 --> 00:12:40,718
I can use the app.

376
00:12:40,958 --> 00:12:42,788
- My gosh.
- I think that's a great idea.

377
00:12:43,018 --> 00:12:44,158
- We can take a taxi.
- Yes.

378
00:12:46,258 --> 00:12:47,658
I had a feeling we might miss it.

379
00:12:48,558 --> 00:12:49,858
What a bummer.

380
00:12:50,728 --> 00:12:53,667
I'm only saying this because it's all in the past now.

381
00:12:53,668 --> 00:12:55,138
If Jeong Min didn't use the toilet...

382
00:12:56,698 --> 00:12:58,838
Me? I see. Is it my fault?

383
00:13:00,638 --> 00:13:02,878
- Well, I'm just saying.
- Hold on. Do we cross here?

384
00:13:03,208 --> 00:13:05,548
- I couldn't control my bladder.
- Wait. Is the bus still there?

385
00:13:06,048 --> 00:13:07,477
- Wait. Is it waiting for us?
- No.

386
00:13:07,478 --> 00:13:09,217
- It just left. My gosh.
- It's going now.

387
00:13:09,218 --> 00:13:10,848
- We should've run.
- It just left.

388
00:13:11,088 --> 00:13:12,388
- Wait.
- Gosh.

389
00:13:12,918 --> 00:13:15,057
In Sung, you would've run if you were younger, right?

390
00:13:15,058 --> 00:13:17,528
My gosh. My knees hurt these days.

391
00:13:19,328 --> 00:13:20,398
Right.

392
00:13:20,528 --> 00:13:22,157
It's been a long time...

393
00:13:22,158 --> 00:13:23,797
since I last walked on the snow in Seoul like this.

394
00:13:23,798 --> 00:13:25,067
(They head to the bus stop while stepping on the show.)

395
00:13:25,068 --> 00:13:26,667
I'm hearing the crunch of the snow under my feet...

396
00:13:26,668 --> 00:13:28,268
- for the first time this year.
- Right.

397
00:13:30,568 --> 00:13:32,267
- Your feet must be freezing.
- They're so cold.

398
00:13:32,268 --> 00:13:34,377
- They're freezing.
- Why did you wear thin-soled shoes?

399
00:13:34,378 --> 00:13:35,577
Jeong Min.

400
00:13:35,578 --> 00:13:37,378
- Why did you wear thin-soled shoes?
- Hey.

401
00:13:38,378 --> 00:13:39,877
Walking in the snow...

402
00:13:39,878 --> 00:13:41,877
- The sun...
- This street is sunny.

403
00:13:41,878 --> 00:13:42,878
(They arrive at the sun-drenched bus stop.)

404
00:13:42,879 --> 00:13:45,187
- You know what?
- It's warm since it's sunny here.

405
00:13:45,188 --> 00:13:47,687
There are so many new apartments in Gangdong now.

406
00:13:47,688 --> 00:13:49,417
- Over there...
- Rice paddies used to be here.

407
00:13:49,418 --> 00:13:51,027
That's probably Dunchon-dong.

408
00:13:51,028 --> 00:13:52,528
- Over there?
- That's probably...

409
00:13:52,828 --> 00:13:54,097
- Right.
- the government-built apartment.

410
00:13:54,098 --> 00:13:56,097
That neighborhood saw its biggest development...

411
00:13:56,098 --> 00:13:58,128
- since the dawn of time.
- I see. It's that neighborhood?

412
00:13:58,768 --> 00:14:00,637
The biggest development since the days of Dangun?

413
00:14:00,638 --> 00:14:02,637
- It's the biggest complex.
- It's the biggest development.

414
00:14:02,638 --> 00:14:03,638
(Trailing off)

415
00:14:03,738 --> 00:14:04,938
- What are you getting at?
- What?

416
00:14:05,738 --> 00:14:06,738
- No, I...
- Are you trying to pick a fight?

417
00:14:06,739 --> 00:14:08,937
- No. So that's the neighborhood?
- With me?

418
00:14:08,938 --> 00:14:10,138
- Do you think you can beat me?
- No.

419
00:14:10,178 --> 00:14:12,377
- "Do you think you can beat me?"
- Do you think you can beat me?

420
00:14:12,378 --> 00:14:13,548
- I can just hit you in the knees.
- "Do you..."

421
00:14:14,878 --> 00:14:16,147
"Do you think you can beat me?"

422
00:14:16,148 --> 00:14:17,348
(Mr. Redevelopment versus New Town Kid)

423
00:14:19,018 --> 00:14:21,658
Hey. We've been waiting for over ten minutes.

424
00:14:21,858 --> 00:14:23,858
No. It hasn't been ten minutes yet.

425
00:14:23,988 --> 00:14:26,287
Right. I knew you'd get cold even though you said you wouldn't.

426
00:14:26,288 --> 00:14:27,597
- Right.
- He acted so tough.

427
00:14:27,598 --> 00:14:29,558
- "It's not cold."
- I'm fine.

428
00:14:29,728 --> 00:14:32,097
In Sung. Do you think this cold weather is getting to me?

429
00:14:32,098 --> 00:14:33,628
Why do you keep looking at Jeong Min?

430
00:14:34,098 --> 00:14:35,238
I'm sorry.

431
00:14:35,368 --> 00:14:37,868
- People need to use the toilet.
- I really had to go.

432
00:14:38,008 --> 00:14:39,208
I'm sorry, Jeong Min.

433
00:14:39,408 --> 00:14:41,008
I find myself keep looking at you.

434
00:14:41,538 --> 00:14:42,708
My gosh, Jeong Min.

435
00:14:43,038 --> 00:14:45,207
Or do you want to stay in the green house for a bit?

436
00:14:45,208 --> 00:14:47,448
- No. That's not ours.
- That's not ours.

437
00:14:47,978 --> 00:14:51,388
Or should we ask someone to give us a ride?

438
00:14:51,588 --> 00:14:52,688
- You want to hitchhike?
- You want to hitchhike?

439
00:14:52,848 --> 00:14:54,018
Gosh, can we do that?

440
00:14:54,418 --> 00:14:56,857
Actually, this is a true story. When I was young...

441
00:14:56,858 --> 00:15:00,927
on our way to our hometown, my father's car broke down.

442
00:15:00,928 --> 00:15:02,797
When it started to get cold, my father...

443
00:15:02,798 --> 00:15:05,897
got a stranger to take me to Wonju, Gangwon Province.

444
00:15:05,898 --> 00:15:07,238
- Really?
- Yes.

445
00:15:08,668 --> 00:15:11,508
- Back then, it was possible.
- Right. People were generous.

446
00:15:11,568 --> 00:15:13,908
I bet you've done something like this too. A long time ago...

447
00:15:14,508 --> 00:15:16,577
when there was traffic on highways, people got out of the cars...

448
00:15:16,578 --> 00:15:18,947
- and walked.
- Of course.

449
00:15:18,948 --> 00:15:20,477
- We still have the footage.
- Yes.

450
00:15:20,478 --> 00:15:21,878
- I've done that too.
- Yes.

451
00:15:22,318 --> 00:15:24,787
Some people grilled pork belly...

452
00:15:24,788 --> 00:15:25,948
- on the side of the highways.
- Right.

453
00:15:26,348 --> 00:15:27,357
What?

454
00:15:27,358 --> 00:15:28,887
- We were just stuck there.
- The cars didn't move at all.

455
00:15:28,888 --> 00:15:29,987
- The local roads were the same.
- They didn't move.

456
00:15:29,988 --> 00:15:31,058
- There was a time like that.
- Yes.

457
00:15:31,358 --> 00:15:33,928
- Wait. It's here.
- There it is. We can take that one.

458
00:15:34,028 --> 00:15:35,258
It's finally here.

459
00:15:35,528 --> 00:15:36,657
Five adults, please.

460
00:15:36,658 --> 00:15:37,767
(The heat inside the bus...)

461
00:15:37,768 --> 00:15:38,997
- We can sit together.
- We're on the bus now.

462
00:15:38,998 --> 00:15:39,998
(warms their cold bodies.)

463
00:15:41,368 --> 00:15:42,567
Hello. Thank you.

464
00:15:42,568 --> 00:15:43,598
(They sit together in the back.)

465
00:15:44,508 --> 00:15:45,907
The bus feels so warm after standing outside.

466
00:15:45,908 --> 00:15:46,938
It's super warm.

467
00:15:48,878 --> 00:15:50,677
- I guess you get cold easily.
- I do.

468
00:15:50,678 --> 00:15:51,907
- Your shoes...
- It's so warm in here.

469
00:15:51,908 --> 00:15:54,818
- You're not warm at all.
- No. Why did I wear these shoes?

470
00:15:55,878 --> 00:15:58,017
- A while ago, Kwang Soo...
- Yes.

471
00:15:58,018 --> 00:16:01,518
attended the awards ceremony of "Pinggyego." Hwang Jung Min...

472
00:16:01,658 --> 00:16:04,128
shushed Kwang Soo like this.

473
00:16:04,528 --> 00:16:07,358
(During the awards ceremony of "Pinggyego")

474
00:16:08,328 --> 00:16:09,628
- Kwang Soo.
- Lee Kwang Soo.

475
00:16:11,728 --> 00:16:14,568
(Kwang Soo is terrified.)

476
00:16:15,068 --> 00:16:16,967
He sent me that clip and asked,

477
00:16:16,968 --> 00:16:18,808
"Do you think he was really angry?"

478
00:16:19,968 --> 00:16:22,808
(He must've been quite scared.)

479
00:16:23,238 --> 00:16:24,378
He got scared.

480
00:16:24,878 --> 00:16:26,008
That's funny.

481
00:16:26,648 --> 00:16:29,617
So did you ask Jung Min?

482
00:16:29,618 --> 00:16:31,887
Yes. I asked him, "Were you really angry?"

483
00:16:31,888 --> 00:16:34,957
Hey, why did you ask him so bluntly?

484
00:16:34,958 --> 00:16:35,958
Kwang Soo was so worried.

485
00:16:37,258 --> 00:16:38,428
He said he was kidding.

486
00:16:38,858 --> 00:16:40,358
Only then was Kwang Soo relieved.

487
00:16:42,628 --> 00:16:44,698
Kwang Soo is so timid.

488
00:16:45,398 --> 00:16:46,598
That's hilarious.

489
00:16:53,138 --> 00:16:54,238
This is so funny.

490
00:16:54,438 --> 00:16:56,838
The sight of In Sung and Hae Joon together from back is funny.

491
00:16:58,748 --> 00:17:01,677
- Office workers on a business trip.
- They look like...

492
00:17:01,678 --> 00:17:02,947
- Like office workers.
- office workers.

493
00:17:02,948 --> 00:17:05,688
Their jackets are giving that vibe of workers on a business trip.

494
00:17:06,248 --> 00:17:09,157
- They don't talk a lot either.
- No, they don't talk much.

495
00:17:09,158 --> 00:17:10,758
(Looking away from each other)

496
00:17:10,988 --> 00:17:13,928
- That's Dunchon Market.
- Okay.

497
00:17:14,198 --> 00:17:15,558
The market has a lot of tasty food.

498
00:17:16,058 --> 00:17:17,528
Inside the traditional market.

499
00:17:17,998 --> 00:17:21,337
I know a great sailfin sandfish restaurant.

500
00:17:21,338 --> 00:17:22,737
The Pacific spiny lumpsucker roe soup is good too.

501
00:17:22,738 --> 00:17:24,168
- Gosh, that sounds good.
- Goodness.

502
00:17:24,308 --> 00:17:26,607
Let's ask In Sung to pick a restaurant for lunch.

503
00:17:26,608 --> 00:17:27,977
- In Sung, pick the lunch spot.
- Let's get his recommendations.

504
00:17:27,978 --> 00:17:29,078
- You're Gangdong's Son.
- But...

505
00:17:29,438 --> 00:17:31,147
Or is there a dish you're craving, Hae Joon?

506
00:17:31,148 --> 00:17:32,148
Me?

507
00:17:32,548 --> 00:17:34,848
- I'm not picky with food.
- Okay.

508
00:17:35,848 --> 00:17:37,548
(Shy)

509
00:17:38,248 --> 00:17:39,848
- Please tell us.
- Tell us.

510
00:17:40,118 --> 00:17:41,218
- You can tell us.
- Tell us.

511
00:17:42,358 --> 00:17:43,688
Let's get something warm.

512
00:17:43,958 --> 00:17:45,088
- Like kalguksu?
- Something warm?

513
00:17:45,228 --> 00:17:46,957
- I'm good with anything.
- Kalguksu sounds good.

514
00:17:46,958 --> 00:17:48,458
- Something warm.
- Noodles are great.

515
00:17:48,628 --> 00:17:50,558
We'll be around Gangdong-gu Office Station.

516
00:17:51,228 --> 00:17:52,827
- Or...
- We can eat after the first one.

517
00:17:52,828 --> 00:17:54,767
I know a great pho restaurant around there.

518
00:17:54,768 --> 00:17:55,797
- Yes. Let's go there.
- Pho sounds good.

519
00:17:55,798 --> 00:17:57,467
- It's in front of Full's house.
- Pho...

520
00:17:57,468 --> 00:17:58,867
- There's a great pho restaurant.
- He knows everything...

521
00:17:58,868 --> 00:18:00,268
about Gangdong.

522
00:18:00,878 --> 00:18:01,978
We're getting off at this stop.

523
00:18:02,908 --> 00:18:05,147
- We're getting off at this stop.
- Talking made the ride feel short.

524
00:18:05,148 --> 00:18:06,707
(It's been 20 minutes and time to get off the bus.)

525
00:18:06,708 --> 00:18:07,918
Have a good day.

526
00:18:08,018 --> 00:18:09,018
Have a good day.

527
00:18:09,019 --> 00:18:10,988
- Happy New Year.
- My gosh.

528
00:18:11,318 --> 00:18:13,348
Watch out here. It's very slippery.

529
00:18:13,518 --> 00:18:14,618
They haven't cleared the snow yet.

530
00:18:14,858 --> 00:18:16,257
Shoes like Jeong Min's...

531
00:18:16,258 --> 00:18:17,658
