- Right.

532
00:18:19,688 --> 00:18:21,458
- I used to do this a lot.
- It's so dangerous here.

533
00:18:25,228 --> 00:18:27,498
(Having fun)

534
00:18:28,438 --> 00:18:29,968
They haven't done anything to clear the street.

535
00:18:30,298 --> 00:18:31,337
They're good.

536
00:18:31,338 --> 00:18:33,508
- Could you step aside for a bit?
- Why? What...

537
00:18:35,708 --> 00:18:37,708
(Gliding smoothly)

538
00:18:37,878 --> 00:18:38,907
There's a patch of ice here.

539
00:18:38,908 --> 00:18:41,318
(Opening up an ice rink in the alley)

540
00:18:42,718 --> 00:18:44,747
My shoes have good resistance.

541
00:18:44,748 --> 00:18:45,987
We should walk on this side.

542
00:18:45,988 --> 00:18:47,148
Be careful.

543
00:18:47,358 --> 00:18:48,388
My gosh.

544
00:18:48,788 --> 00:18:51,588
(The middle-aged kids won't listen.)

545
00:18:53,758 --> 00:18:55,598
(Having a blast)

546
00:18:56,298 --> 00:18:58,367
(They glide to the first spare time spot.)

547
00:18:58,368 --> 00:18:59,398
It's not here?

548
00:19:00,838 --> 00:19:02,167
The building number is 49.

549
00:19:02,168 --> 00:19:03,168
(I cut, tap, and make holes.)

550
00:19:03,169 --> 00:19:04,268
It's on the first floor.

551
00:19:04,938 --> 00:19:07,238
- The first floor?
- Is it that one? No?

552
00:19:07,738 --> 00:19:09,077
- That's a flower shop.
- It's a flower shop.

553
00:19:09,078 --> 00:19:10,108
It's a flower shop.

554
00:19:10,638 --> 00:19:12,408
- What's the building number?
- Or the bicycle shop?

555
00:19:12,548 --> 00:19:14,078
Usually, we can tell.

556
00:19:14,178 --> 00:19:16,678
- Where's the building number?
- Or they stand outside for us.

557
00:19:17,518 --> 00:19:19,688
- Is this the one?
- There it is. "Leather and Craft."

558
00:19:19,718 --> 00:19:20,887
- I see.
- You startled me.

559
00:19:20,888 --> 00:19:22,257
- It's 1 of these 2.
- It's over there.

560
00:19:22,258 --> 00:19:23,917
- I think this is the one.
- My gosh. It's that one.

561
00:19:23,918 --> 00:19:25,187
- I see. This is the one.
- What a cool shop.

562
00:19:25,188 --> 00:19:26,558
- I see.
- His workshop is here.

563
00:19:26,628 --> 00:19:27,927
- How cool.
- This is so cool.

564
00:19:27,928 --> 00:19:29,028
This is really cool.

565
00:19:29,328 --> 00:19:31,168
- Kim Sin Woong.
- My gosh. Look at that.

566
00:19:31,868 --> 00:19:34,237
- The motorcycle...
- This has to be the one.

567
00:19:34,238 --> 00:19:35,297
(Is it the shop with a cool motorcycle?)

568
00:19:35,298 --> 00:19:36,298
- This is the place.
- It's so cool.

569
00:19:36,299 --> 00:19:37,637
- It's a leather workshop.
- This place is so cool.

570
00:19:37,638 --> 00:19:39,468
- Hello.
- Hello.

571
00:19:39,568 --> 00:19:40,668
(Amazed)

572
00:19:41,078 --> 00:19:42,138
This is so cool.

573
00:19:42,208 --> 00:19:44,207
- Look at this place.
- This place is amazing.

574
00:19:44,208 --> 00:19:45,807
- Hello.
- I thought I was in the States.

575
00:19:45,808 --> 00:19:48,018
- My gosh.
- This place is so cool.

576
00:19:49,648 --> 00:19:51,147
(Amazed)

577
00:19:51,148 --> 00:19:52,618
(Cheering)

578
00:19:54,088 --> 00:19:55,957
- I thought you were a cowboy.
- Hello.

579
00:19:55,958 --> 00:19:57,057
Hello.

580
00:19:57,058 --> 00:19:58,227
(Whenever Guest, Kim Sin Woong)

581
00:19:58,228 --> 00:20:00,227
(Starstruck)

582
00:20:00,228 --> 00:20:02,828
- Seriously. What a cool place.
- Thank you.

583
00:20:03,098 --> 00:20:04,767
People who love motorcycles...

584
00:20:04,768 --> 00:20:06,427
- would go crazy here.
- He has helmets here too.

585
00:20:06,428 --> 00:20:08,197
(It looks like a scene straight out of a Western movie.)

586
00:20:08,198 --> 00:20:09,798
Guys would go crazy here.

587
00:20:11,568 --> 00:20:13,937
People who love motorcycles would go crazy here.

588
00:20:13,938 --> 00:20:15,378
(A craft workshop where he makes all kinds of leather goods)

589
00:20:16,478 --> 00:20:18,307
Gosh, this is a cool place.

590
00:20:18,308 --> 00:20:19,747
(They feel like they've become gunfighters of the Wild West.)

591
00:20:19,748 --> 00:20:22,078
- Is this your usual work attire?
- Yes.

592
00:20:22,178 --> 00:20:24,787
I must make sure I always look the part.

593
00:20:24,788 --> 00:20:26,188
(Dressed in a Western-themed outfit)

594
00:20:26,488 --> 00:20:28,518
I wore a tracksuit one day.

595
00:20:29,688 --> 00:20:31,427
And I was quite embarrassed.

596
00:20:31,428 --> 00:20:34,027
- Why?
- This is like a community lounge.

597
00:20:34,028 --> 00:20:35,827
Do a lot of local residents come here?

598
00:20:35,828 --> 00:20:38,167
Yes. My friends and customers often visit.

599
00:20:38,168 --> 00:20:39,627
(He always dresses appropriately for his visitors.)

600
00:20:39,628 --> 00:20:41,267
Even first-time customers and I become good friends.

601
00:20:41,268 --> 00:20:42,897
That's how I am.

602
00:20:42,898 --> 00:20:45,207
- I can befriend everyone I meet.
- I see.

603
00:20:45,208 --> 00:20:47,477
I once spent ten hours with a first-time customer.

604
00:20:47,478 --> 00:20:48,938
We even had a meal together.

605
00:20:49,378 --> 00:20:51,247
- You had a meal with him?
- Isn't that a bit weird?

606
00:20:51,248 --> 00:20:55,147
No. He's on the national skiing team.

607
00:20:55,148 --> 00:20:58,418
He said he wanted to make hats and so on.

608
00:20:58,548 --> 00:21:00,017
Once we started to talk...

609
00:21:00,018 --> 00:21:01,618
- You spent ten hours with him?
- Yes.

610
00:21:02,288 --> 00:21:04,657
- That explains your accessories...
- Yes.

611
00:21:04,658 --> 00:21:05,857
- and your hairstyle.
- Right.

612
00:21:05,858 --> 00:21:06,928
(Flashy accessories and long curly hair)

613
00:21:07,388 --> 00:21:10,428
(His fancy outfits allow him to welcome customers whenever.)

614
00:21:11,098 --> 00:21:12,667
We saw the motorcycle from Ural Motorcycles out front.

615
00:21:12,668 --> 00:21:14,337
- Yes. You know the brand.
- Yes.

616
00:21:14,338 --> 00:21:15,597
(A cool retro motorcycle goes everywhere with him.)

617
00:21:15,598 --> 00:21:16,867
Right. It's got that vibe.

618
00:21:16,868 --> 00:21:17,868
(Sin Woong with an unusual vibe)

619
00:21:17,869 --> 00:21:19,008
His vibe is unusual.

620
00:21:19,068 --> 00:21:20,068
You're so cool.

621
00:21:20,069 --> 00:21:21,108
- Thank you.
- You're really cool.

622
00:21:21,478 --> 00:21:22,577
Thank you.

623
00:21:22,578 --> 00:21:25,877
By the way, I'm seeing many different kinds of leather goods.

624
00:21:25,878 --> 00:21:28,247
Yes. I try my best...

625
00:21:28,248 --> 00:21:30,318
to work at least for 15 hours here.

626
00:21:31,018 --> 00:21:32,947
I want to introduce as many products as possible.

627
00:21:32,948 --> 00:21:35,487
If you work for 15 hours, when do you start and finish?

628
00:21:35,488 --> 00:21:38,157
I start working at 10am and finish around...

629
00:21:38,158 --> 00:21:39,227
- Around late at night?
- midnight. Yes.

630
00:21:39,228 --> 00:21:40,857
- Until late at night?
- Yes. I work alone.

631
00:21:40,858 --> 00:21:42,227
Do you take the weekend off?

632
00:21:42,228 --> 00:21:43,228
No, I don't.

633
00:21:43,928 --> 00:21:45,597
- What? You...
- You should take a day off.

634
00:21:45,598 --> 00:21:48,137
Tell me. Is someone forcing you?

635
00:21:48,138 --> 00:21:49,937
- You're not being held here, right?
- Is someone abusing you?

636
00:21:49,938 --> 00:21:51,007
No, that's not the case.

637
00:21:51,008 --> 00:21:53,138
But how can you work even on weekends?

638
00:21:53,308 --> 00:21:56,507
I must always work diligently.

639
00:21:56,508 --> 00:21:59,207
Gosh. Tell us about the helmets. Do you make them too?

640
00:21:59,208 --> 00:22:01,077
I also make custom helmets.

641
00:22:01,078 --> 00:22:02,917
I make the leather cover on the helmets.

642
00:22:02,918 --> 00:22:05,047
- You also make those covers?
- But I'll stop doing that now.

643
00:22:05,048 --> 00:22:07,687
- My fingers are now twisted.
- Gosh.

644
00:22:07,688 --> 00:22:09,017
They're twisted.

645
00:22:09,018 --> 00:22:10,487
- I...
- Yes. They're indeed twisted.

646
00:22:10,488 --> 00:22:11,787
They're twisted.

647
00:22:11,788 --> 00:22:13,488
- From working too hard?
- Yes.

648
00:22:13,728 --> 00:22:16,428
I can untwist them when I turn them like this.

649
00:22:19,298 --> 00:22:20,668
I can untwist them.

650
00:22:21,938 --> 00:22:24,097
Anyway, Sin Woong's day...

651
00:22:24,098 --> 00:22:27,107
can be quite mundane sometimes.

652
00:22:27,108 --> 00:22:28,637
We should make his day fun...

653
00:22:28,638 --> 00:22:30,207
- and give him presents.
- That's right.

654
00:22:30,208 --> 00:22:32,377
Who wants to cast the dice?

655
00:22:32,378 --> 00:22:33,378
(Picking Jeong Min)

656
00:22:33,379 --> 00:22:34,448
- Me?
- You go first.

657
00:22:34,818 --> 00:22:36,918
- He's the fiery type.
- You go first.

658
00:22:37,078 --> 00:22:38,787
- Me?
- When you look at us,

659
00:22:38,788 --> 00:22:42,588
we look like we're visiting a Korean resident in the States.

660
00:22:43,018 --> 00:22:44,627
- I mean, when you look at us...
- It feels like we're in the States.

661
00:22:44,628 --> 00:22:47,358
- It feels like we're in the States.
- Right.

662
00:22:47,528 --> 00:22:49,458
- Jeong Min, why don't you try?
- Okay.

663
00:22:49,628 --> 00:22:50,798
- Toss it here?
- Yes.

664
00:22:53,068 --> 00:22:54,068
Don't let it be zero.

665
00:22:54,069 --> 00:22:55,298
(Let's just avoid rolling a 0.)

666
00:22:56,198 --> 00:22:57,767
(0 coupons)

667
00:22:57,768 --> 00:22:59,238
- Don't let it be zero.
- Gosh, you...

668
00:22:59,438 --> 00:23:01,578
- No. They were supposed to explain.
- You...

669
00:23:01,738 --> 00:23:03,107
- You did it before they got to.
- But...

670
00:23:03,108 --> 00:23:05,348
- You know what?
- Try again.

671
00:23:05,808 --> 00:23:07,148
- It's zero.
- What...

672
00:23:07,408 --> 00:23:08,478
It's zero.

673
00:23:09,518 --> 00:23:11,318
Jeong Min...

674
00:23:11,688 --> 00:23:13,948
- Nice try.
- No bonus tries for us today.

675
00:23:14,588 --> 00:23:15,617
All right. Let's begin.

676
00:23:15,618 --> 00:23:16,687
Let's start by checking the prize...

677
00:23:16,688 --> 00:23:17,757
- for Round One.
- Let's check it.

678
00:23:17,758 --> 00:23:19,688
- Crack the first fortune cookie.
- My gosh.

679
00:23:19,928 --> 00:23:21,557
- Gosh, there are fortune cookies.
- All right.

680
00:23:21,558 --> 00:23:23,027
- You run a publishing house.
- Sure.

681
00:23:23,028 --> 00:23:24,727
"My shop is known..."

682
00:23:24,728 --> 00:23:26,467
"as the community lounge of Gangdong-gu."

683
00:23:26,468 --> 00:23:28,797
"So I hope it's always filled with the smell of coffee."

684
00:23:28,798 --> 00:23:30,367
"Nespresso coffee machine."

685
00:23:30,368 --> 00:23:32,367
(Round 1 prize: A high-end coffee machine)

686
00:23:32,368 --> 00:23:33,537
Do you like coffee?

687
00:23:33,538 --> 00:23:35,178
- Yes. I drink it every day.
- I see.

688
00:23:35,378 --> 00:23:37,437
- This is the community lounge.
- Right.

689
00:23:37,438 --> 00:23:39,378
- A coffee machine.
- Nice.

690
00:23:39,508 --> 00:23:41,747
(Ruler Alkkagi)

691
00:23:41,748 --> 00:23:43,317
(Round 1)

692
00:23:43,318 --> 00:23:46,218
(Flick the 2 buttons that are on the ruler.)

693
00:23:47,418 --> 00:23:49,558
- With a button?
- The buttons.

694
00:23:50,258 --> 00:23:51,458
- What?
- So this is...

695
00:23:51,558 --> 00:23:52,587
How do we play the game?

696
00:23:52,588 --> 00:23:53,987
Let's give it a shot.

697
00:23:53,988 --> 00:23:55,098
(Staring)

698
00:23:55,258 --> 00:23:57,158
Is this how you do it? Like flick it over.

699
00:23:57,768 --> 00:24:00,367
I got it. So flick that button and the other one over there.

700
00:24:00,368 --> 00:24:02,267
- I think so.
- I see.

701
00:24:02,268 --> 00:24:03,998
We have to flick each one in order.

702
00:24:04,838 --> 00:24:06,007
- We five have to flick...
- Try it.

703
00:24:06,008 --> 00:24:07,337
- the two over.
- Correct.

704
00:24:07,338 --> 00:24:09,177
We simply have to flick them over.

705
00:24:09,178 --> 00:24:11,448
- It looks quite easy.
- Is it okay if ours fall?

706
00:24:12,078 --> 00:24:13,907
- This is...
- Aiming is hard.

707
00:24:13,908 --> 00:24:15,948
- The button has to go straight.
- It's far away.

708
00:24:17,718 --> 00:24:18,848
Can't we start from here?

709
00:24:19,088 --> 00:24:20,717
- Of course.
- We can start here, right?

710
00:24:20,718 --> 00:24:21,758
No, not there.

711
00:24:22,358 --> 00:24:23,588
How can we flick it over?

712
00:24:23,858 --> 00:24:25,257
- Sorry?
- We can't flick it over.

713
00:24:25,258 --> 00:24:26,987
- Just a tad bit.
- You still have to start there.

714
00:24:26,988 --> 00:24:28,158
It's...

715
00:24:29,598 --> 00:24:30,728
- This is...
- What?

716
00:24:30,898 --> 00:24:32,367
It's tougher than I imagined.

717
00:24:32,368 --> 00:24:33,767
The other side is long.

718
00:24:33,768 --> 00:24:34,898
That's the hardest part.

719
00:24:35,668 --> 00:24:36,697
The button we use...

720
00:24:36,698 --> 00:24:37,738
- doesn't matter, right?
- No.

721
00:24:37,938 --> 00:24:39,437
Isn't bigger better?

722
00:24:39,438 --> 00:24:40,438
- Oh, no.
- Right?

723
00:24:41,008 --> 00:24:42,407
- It's...
- We're in trouble.

724
00:24:42,408 --> 00:24:43,537
- Controlling your strength...
- I think...

725
00:24:43,538 --> 00:24:44,678
- isn't easy.
- we should flick hard.

726
00:24:46,078 --> 00:24:47,878
Mine flies off the ruler.

727
00:24:48,978 --> 00:24:50,517
- The button flies.
- Hold on.

728
00:24:50,518 --> 00:24:52,118
- Hae Joon.
- This is good.

729
00:24:52,818 --> 00:24:53,847
Come on.

730
00:24:53,848 --> 00:24:54,918
(Laughing)

731
00:24:55,658 --> 00:24:56,787
Hold on a minute.

732
00:24:56,788 --> 00:24:58,787
- I'll...
- Don't flick it hard.

733
00:24:58,788 --> 00:25:00,057
I'll make it.

734
00:25:00,058 --> 00:25:01,827
- That's it.
- Sending it down straight is...

735
00:25:01,828 --> 00:25:04,058
- Flick it straight.
