00:42:12,685 --> 00:42:15,685
We're in Round 3, okay? Round 3.

1234
00:42:15,785 --> 00:42:17,224
The three of us can take turns...

1235
00:42:17,225 --> 00:42:18,995
- to eliminate it.
- Yes.

1236
00:42:19,425 --> 00:42:20,754
(Only the 3 of "HUMINT" are left!)

1237
00:42:20,755 --> 00:42:21,865
Don't overdo it.

1238
00:42:23,665 --> 00:42:25,165
- Just to the middle.
- The middle.

1239
00:42:25,435 --> 00:42:26,695
The middle, Jeong Min.

1240
00:42:30,505 --> 00:42:33,404
(How...)

1241
00:42:33,405 --> 00:42:35,504
(did that...)

1242
00:42:35,505 --> 00:42:37,975
(happen?)

1243
00:42:41,145 --> 00:42:42,745
(He got to the goal button in one hit!)

1244
00:42:44,785 --> 00:42:46,885
(Jeong Min finished it.)

1245
00:42:47,115 --> 00:42:48,985
(Screaming)

1246
00:42:49,785 --> 00:42:52,094
- What?
- Did we do it?

1247
00:42:52,095 --> 00:42:53,394
- Success!
- Yes!

1248
00:42:53,395 --> 00:42:54,855
(They cleanly pass Round 3.)

1249
00:42:55,025 --> 00:42:57,725
- Park Jeong Min!
- Park Jeong Min!

1250
00:42:57,965 --> 00:43:00,394
(Round 1,)

1251
00:43:00,395 --> 00:43:03,264
(Round 2,)

1252
00:43:03,265 --> 00:43:07,435
(and Round 3 were all finished by Jeong Min.)

1253
00:43:09,105 --> 00:43:11,104
- How did you do that?
- Were you planning on doing that?

1254
00:43:11,105 --> 00:43:12,345
No, I wasn't.

1255
00:43:13,545 --> 00:43:14,644
Seriously.

1256
00:43:14,645 --> 00:43:16,414
(The energy of success fills the workshop.)

1257
00:43:16,415 --> 00:43:17,514
Jeong Min!

1258
00:43:17,515 --> 00:43:19,214
- This adrenaline rush...
- I'm so glad.

1259
00:43:19,215 --> 00:43:20,285
Right?

1260
00:43:20,385 --> 00:43:22,055
- You feel it, right?
- It's a dopamine rush.

1261
00:43:22,555 --> 00:43:23,824
A coffee machine,

1262
00:43:23,825 --> 00:43:25,454
- a resort voucher...
- A voucher.

1263
00:43:25,455 --> 00:43:27,224
- He's rich now.
- And an air purifier.

1264
00:43:27,225 --> 00:43:28,294
You also get...

1265
00:43:28,295 --> 00:43:31,294
- our merch.
- Thank you.

1266
00:43:31,295 --> 00:43:33,034
I feel great today.

1267
00:43:33,035 --> 00:43:35,735
- We're off to a good start.
- In Sung was...

1268
00:43:36,065 --> 00:43:39,005
When I hit it there, everyone was happy, but only In Sung was...

1269
00:43:40,635 --> 00:43:42,374
- The pressure of going last.
- He had to go last.

1270
00:43:42,375 --> 00:43:43,905
- Right.
- Because of the pressure.

1271
00:43:43,975 --> 00:43:45,614
Congratulations once again.

1272
00:43:45,615 --> 00:43:46,974
- Thank you.
- Congrats.

1273
00:43:46,975 --> 00:43:48,345
(These 5 men are on a roll after passing Round 3.)

1274
00:43:49,945 --> 00:43:50,945
Jeong Min.

1275
00:43:50,946 --> 00:43:52,055
(Hero Park Jeong Min is here.)

1276
00:43:52,115 --> 00:43:53,614
- I didn't intend it, but...
- You did great.

1277
00:43:53,615 --> 00:43:54,985
You're not even wearing a scarf now?

1278
00:43:55,125 --> 00:43:56,125
No.

1279
00:43:56,285 --> 00:43:58,425
I guess you don't even feel cold after that success.

1280
00:43:58,755 --> 00:43:59,795
(Exclaiming)

1281
00:44:01,155 --> 00:44:03,025
So, this is the taste of success.

1282
00:44:03,665 --> 00:44:04,725
This is it.

1283
00:44:05,395 --> 00:44:07,364
- It feels good, right, Jeong Min?
- I feel great.

1284
00:44:07,365 --> 00:44:08,665
(I'm exhilarated.)

1285
00:44:08,805 --> 00:44:09,935
Are we going to play another game?

1286
00:44:10,605 --> 00:44:12,205
- After we eat.
- Oh, after lunch.

1287
00:44:13,075 --> 00:44:14,535
- This is good.
- I feel amazing.

1288
00:44:15,245 --> 00:44:18,445
- Hae Joon, do you feel good?
- I feel great.

1289
00:44:18,615 --> 00:44:19,745
That's awesome.

1290
00:44:19,875 --> 00:44:22,014
- What's our next destination?
- Let's check it.

1291
00:44:22,015 --> 00:44:23,144
(Checking the next spare time spot)

1292
00:44:23,145 --> 00:44:24,285
Where is this?

1293
00:44:24,345 --> 00:44:25,585
Yangjae-daero?

1294
00:44:25,785 --> 00:44:27,114
- Yangjae-dong?
- It must be near Myeongil-dong.

1295
00:44:27,115 --> 00:44:28,355
- Myeongil-dong?
- Yes.

1296
00:44:28,555 --> 00:44:29,954
You got it right away.

1297
00:44:29,955 --> 00:44:31,185
(Gangdong's Son figured out the location instantly.)

1298
00:44:32,295 --> 00:44:34,255
(Myeongil-dong?)

1299
00:44:34,355 --> 00:44:35,525
This isn't a good route.

1300
00:44:36,225 --> 00:44:37,324
- Hey.
- We have to take a cab.

1301
00:44:37,325 --> 00:44:38,495
Yes.

1302
00:44:39,135 --> 00:44:40,135
We have to take a taxi.

1303
00:44:40,295 --> 00:44:41,935
(Grinning)

1304
00:44:42,005 --> 00:44:44,905
(The corners of his mouth turn up after hearing a taxi.)

1305
00:44:45,635 --> 00:44:46,635
- Should I call one?
- How...

1306
00:44:46,636 --> 00:44:47,835
(Should I call a taxi?)

1307
00:44:49,175 --> 00:44:51,244
- Or we can eat around here.
- Lunch?

1308
00:44:51,245 --> 00:44:52,414
We could do that.

1309
00:44:52,415 --> 00:44:56,044
- Walk 13 minutes that way, - Okay.

1310
00:44:56,045 --> 00:44:57,045
and there's a pho place.

1311
00:44:57,046 --> 00:44:58,384
- Let's go.
- The one you mentioned?

1312
00:44:58,385 --> 00:44:59,814
- Let's go there.
- Come on.

1313
00:44:59,815 --> 00:45:02,024
- We'll go there, then.
- Pho.

1314
00:45:02,025 --> 00:45:03,454
- Pho.
- Pho sounds good.

1315
00:45:03,455 --> 00:45:04,555
It sounds delicious.

1316
00:45:04,955 --> 00:45:06,124
I can't believe we did it.

1317
00:45:06,125 --> 00:45:07,594
(Giggling)

1318
00:45:07,595 --> 00:45:08,725
We did it.

1319
00:45:09,665 --> 00:45:10,665
- It feels so good, doesn't it?
- Yes.

1320
00:45:10,666 --> 00:45:11,965
(They can't help but smile.)

1321
00:45:12,265 --> 00:45:13,634
It's been a while since I last had pho.

1322
00:45:13,635 --> 00:45:15,834
(It's 12:07pm, the peak of the lunch hour.)

1323
00:45:15,835 --> 00:45:16,934
Did you often go there?

1324
00:45:16,935 --> 00:45:17,935
With Kang Full.

1325
00:45:18,635 --> 00:45:19,775
- Really?
- Yes.

1326
00:45:21,845 --> 00:45:23,944
- When we were filming "Hwayi,"
- Yes.

1327
00:45:23,945 --> 00:45:25,645
we used to drink soju every day...

1328
00:45:25,745 --> 00:45:28,845
- in Kim Yun Seok's room.
- Every day.

1329
00:45:29,015 --> 00:45:31,285
- Was that...
- It's been over a decade.

1330
00:45:32,485 --> 00:45:34,855
- At the time...
- We were both...

1331
00:45:34,885 --> 00:45:36,754
- We were rookies.
- Total rookies.

1332
00:45:36,755 --> 00:45:37,784
(They spent their rookie years together.)

1333
00:45:37,785 --> 00:45:39,025
It was my first time.

1334
00:45:39,255 --> 00:45:40,324
I barely knew anything...

1335
00:45:40,325 --> 00:45:41,355
- about filming movies.
- Right.

1336
00:45:42,865 --> 00:45:44,295
I guess we're just going there.

1337
00:45:44,395 --> 00:45:46,595
- Yes, we keep it real.
- Right.

1338
00:45:47,995 --> 00:45:50,405
Walking in the cold like this...

1339
00:45:50,765 --> 00:45:52,434
- makes me crave it more.
- Does it?

1340
00:45:52,435 --> 00:45:53,734
- It makes me crave pho.
- It must be so good.

1341
00:45:53,735 --> 00:45:54,975
I'm going insane.

1342
00:45:55,575 --> 00:45:56,675
I'm dying to eat it.

1343
00:45:58,245 --> 00:45:59,544
Isn't it on our right?

1344
00:45:59,545 --> 00:46:01,114
- Bangkok?
- You're right.

1345
00:46:01,115 --> 00:46:02,885
Let's see. Here it is.

1346
00:46:04,445 --> 00:46:05,514
It's not that big.

1347
00:46:05,515 --> 00:46:06,714
(They arrive at the pho place recommended by Gangdong's Son.)

1348
00:46:06,715 --> 00:46:07,715
- Wait.
- Can we go in?

1349
00:46:07,716 --> 00:46:08,985
- No way.
- I think there's a line.

1350
00:46:09,925 --> 00:46:11,655
(Glancing)

1351
00:46:12,355 --> 00:46:13,824
(In Sung quickly moves.)

1352
00:46:13,825 --> 00:46:14,925
Is there a line?

1353
00:46:15,695 --> 00:46:17,164
- I think it's full.
- Are they closed?

1354
00:46:17,165 --> 00:46:18,535
No, it says, "Open."

1355
00:46:18,695 --> 00:46:19,734
- There are people, though.
- Are there a lot of people?

1356
00:46:19,735 --> 00:46:21,634
- There are.
- They're waiting in line.

1357
00:46:21,635 --> 00:46:23,864
- It must be a popular place.
- It's popular, isn't it?

1358
00:46:23,865 --> 00:46:25,235
- I don't think we can eat it.
- I want it even more.

1359
00:46:25,635 --> 00:46:26,904
I'm sure they'll be done soon.

1360
00:46:26,905 --> 00:46:28,604
- Let's ask.
- Let's see.

1361
00:46:28,605 --> 00:46:30,005
How long do you think we'll have to wait?

1362
00:46:30,505 --> 00:46:32,314
- How many in your party?
- Five.

1363
00:46:32,315 --> 00:46:33,645
- Just a second.
- Soon?

1364
00:46:34,715 --> 00:46:36,385
We have to find another place if we can't go in.

1365
00:46:36,415 --> 00:46:37,544
(Thinking)

1366
00:46:37,545 --> 00:46:38,714
- Somewhere else.
- Oh, my.

1367
00:46:38,715 --> 00:46:40,314
There's a good gukbap place...

1368
00:46:40,315 --> 00:46:41,514
over there.

1369
00:46:41,515 --> 00:46:43,784
- Gukbap sounds nice.
- Yes.

1370
00:46:43,785 --> 00:46:44,785
(Gangdong's Son comes up with Plan B right away.)

1371
00:46:44,786 --> 00:46:45,855
It's...

1372
00:46:46,695 --> 00:46:47,924
It'll take 15 to 20 minutes.

1373
00:46:47,925 --> 00:46:48,964
About 15 to 20?

1374
00:46:48,965 --> 00:46:50,024
- We're full now.
- Right.

1375
00:46:50,025 --> 00:46:51,394
- We were...
- Okay.

1376
00:46:51,395 --> 00:46:53,094
- All right. Thank you.
- Thank you.

1377
00:46:53,095 --> 00:46:54,394
- Thank you.
- It's 20 minutes.

1378
00:46:54,395 --> 00:46:55,605
- Hello.
- I'll go and check.

1379
00:46:55,965 --> 00:46:57,164
- Are we going?
- Over there...

1380
00:46:57,165 --> 00:46:58,504
- No, I'll go and check.
- Where?

1381
00:46:58,505 --> 00:46:59,775
I'll come with you.

1382
00:46:59,935 --> 00:47:01,905
- Where?
- There's a place down there.

1383
00:47:01,975 --> 00:47:03,874
- Wait here.
- Wait here.

1384
00:47:03,875 --> 00:47:05,574
- He said to wait.
- Where are you going?

1385
00:47:05,575 --> 00:47:07,774
- He and I will go and check.
- The gukbap place.

1386
00:47:07,775 --> 00:47:08,785
Okay.

1387
00:47:10,145 --> 00:47:11,854
(With a responsible look)

1388
00:47:11,855 --> 00:47:13,314
- Where is it?
- This way.

1389
00:47:13,315 --> 00:47:14,755
(They stride toward the gukbap place.)

1390
00:47:16,985 --> 00:47:18,155
If we can't eat, then...

1391
00:47:19,825 --> 00:47:21,155
Maybe Lotteria.

1392
00:47:22,095 --> 00:47:23,525
I was thinking the same thing.

1393
00:47:24,295 --> 00:47:25,395
They also have a Burger King.

1394
00:47:26,465 --> 00:47:27,635
I'd be fine with that.

1395
00:47:28,335 --> 00:47:29,635
It's nice to eat...

1396
00:47:29,835 --> 00:47:31,134
- at a popular restaurant, - Right.

1397
00:47:31,135 --> 00:47:32,504
- but I'm fine with anything.
- Me too.

1398
00:47:32,505 --> 00:47:33,505
(Jeong Min is the same.)

1399
00:47:33,506 --> 00:47:34,534
What about you, Hae Joon?

1400
00:47:34,535 --> 00:47:36,174
I'm actually fine with anything.

1401
00:47:36,175 --> 00:47:37,445
Right?

1402
00:47:37,475 --> 00:47:38,545
We're all...

1403
00:47:38,945 --> 00:47:40,414
I would even eat at a convenience store.

1404
00:47:40,415 --> 00:47:42,284
- We think alike.
- Even a convenience store.

1405
00:47:42,285 --> 00:47:43,545
I could eat at a convenience store.

1406
00:47:44,485 --> 00:47:46,784
You know this neighborhood inside and out.

1407
00:47:46,785 --> 00:47:49,225
- I've been here often.
- I see.

1408
00:47:50,355 --> 00:47:53,494
Are you not the type to wait in line for food?

1409
00:47:53,495 --> 00:47:54,954
Wait. Why is this place open?

1410
00:47:54,955 --> 00:47:55,995
What?

1411
00:47:56,195 --> 00:47:58,024
Hello. I saw that the door was open.

1412
00:47:58,025 --> 00:47:59,164
Where's the owner?

1413
00:47:59,165 --> 00:48:01,065
(He naturally says hi.)

1414
00:48:01,135 --> 00:48:02,435
What? He hasn't come in yet?

1415
00:48:05,835 --> 00:48:08,274
You know the entire neighborhood.

1416
00:48:08,275 --> 00:48:09,345
Yes, I know that place.

1417
00:48:09,445 --> 00:48:11,144
- A bar you go to after dinner?
- Yes.

1418
00:48:11,145 --> 00:48:13,215
- Exactly.
- It looks perfect.

1419
00:48:15,415 --> 00:48:16,484
- Is this it?
- Yes.

1420
00:48:16,485 --> 00:48:17,485
Oh, this place.

1421
00:48:17,885 --> 00:48:19,215
This looks good too.

1422
00:48:20,785 --> 00:48:22,355
- We won't be able to eat here.
- We can't.

1423
00:48:23,185 --> 00:48:24,484
- We need two tables.
- You'll have to wait.

1424
00:48:24,485 --> 00:48:26,124
You can come in when we have two tables.

1425
00:48:26,125 --> 00:48:27,224
- Two tables.
- Yes.

1426
00:48:27,225 --> 00:48:28,255
- Then...
- Okay.

1427
00:48:28,695 --> 00:48:30,624
Group 1 can wait here, while Group 2 can wait there.

1428
00:48:30,625 --> 00:48:31,795
We can eat at the place that serves us first.

1429
00:48:32,035 --> 00:48:33,365
We don't have to stay together the whole time.

1430
00:48:33,995 --> 00:48:35,534
We can pick one place...

1431
00:48:35,535 --> 00:48:36,664
and wait there together.

1432
00:48:36,665 --> 00:48:37,705
Really?

1433
00:48:37,835 --> 00:48:39,035
Call Jae Suk.

1434
00:48:40,935 --> 00:48:42,544
(Checking Group 1's situation)

1435
00:48:42,545 --> 00:48:43,575
Hey, Yeon Shik.

1436
00:48:43,705 --> 00:48:46,914
How long do you think it'll take? We have to wait for this place too.

1437
00:48:46,915 --> 00:48:48,714
(A two-way live broadcast)

1438
00:48:48,715 --> 00:48:51,445
It'll only be five minutes here.

1439
00:48:52,685 --> 00:48:54,754
Okay. Then, we should...

1440
00:48:54,755 --> 00:48:56,384
- We'll go.
- We'll go there, then.

1441
00:48:56,385 --> 00:48:57,525
That sounds better.

1442
00:48:58,755 --> 00:49:00,695
- What?
- We're coming.

1443
00:49:00,925 --> 00:49:02,125
- Yes, come on over.
- Okay.

1444
00:49:02,565 --> 00:49:04,824
That must also be a popular place.

1445
00:49:04,825 --> 00:49:05,965
Exactly.

1446
00:49:06,195 --> 00:49:09,165
- But it's lunchtime, so...
- Yes.

1447
00:49:09,805 --> 00:49:12,534
He's the guy that said, "Falling in love isn't a crime."

1448
00:49:12,535 --> 00:49:14,105
- "Falling in love isn't a crime."
- What?

1449
00:49:14,705 --> 00:49:16,705
Someone said, "Falling in love isn't a crime."

1450
00:49:17,975 --> 00:49:19,044
Who said that?

1451
00:49:19,045 --> 00:49:20,745
- Someone inside.
- "Falling in love isn't a crime."

1452
00:49:21,315 --> 00:49:23,784
"Those three were in a movie. That's him!"

1453
00:49:23,785 --> 00:49:25,715
- "Falling in love isn't a crime."
- "Falling in love isn't a crime."

1454
00:49:26,015 --> 00:49:27,154
They don't really know my name.

1455
00:49:27,155 --> 00:49:28,155
Right.

1456
00:49:28,156 --> 00:49:30,824
Just a guy who played Kim Hee Ae's husband.

1457
00:49:30,825 --> 00:49:31,885
They don't know my name.

1458
00:49:31,955 --> 00:49:33,654
"That's Kim Hee Ae's husband!"

1459
00:49:33,655 --> 00:49:35,325
(Hae Joon is better-known for his line.)

1460
00:49:36,265 --> 00:49:37,294
That's funny.

1461
00:49:37,295 --> 00:49:38,295
(Looking)

1462
00:49:39,835 --> 00:49:42,335
Why don't we stay in the sunlight?

1463
00:49:42,435 --> 00:49:43,505
In the sun.

1464
00:49:43,605 --> 00:49:45,035
It's slightly warmer here.

1465
00:49:45,375 --> 00:49:47,675
Hae Joon is such a golden boy.

1466
00:49:48,005 --> 00:49:49,005
He's like the golden boy.

1467
00:49:51,105 --> 00:49:54,275
(Seeing the sun isn't a crime.)

1468
00:49:54,815 --> 00:49:55,815
There they come.

1469
00:49:56,215 --> 00:49:57,915
That place also had good gukbap.

1470
00:49:58,285 --> 00:50:00,084
- I think we can go in soon.
- Yes.

1471
00:50:00,085 --> 00:50:01,354
- It won't take long.
- Right.

1472
00:50:01,355 --> 00:50:02,625
- Can we sit now?
- Yes.

1473
00:50:03,155 --> 00:50:04,384
- Thank you.
- Hello.

1474
00:50:04,385 --> 00:50:06,355
(They enter after 15 minutes of waiting.)

1475
00:50:07,625 --> 00:50:09,624
We'll eat these two like side dishes.

1476
00:50:09,625 --> 00:50:11,594
- Okay.
- And one bowl of pho for each.

1477
00:50:11,595 --> 00:50:12,635
Good.

1478
00:50:13,165 --> 00:50:14,635
- I'll have a regular pho.
- Me too.

1479
00:50:14,735 --> 00:50:17,365
One tom yum kung pho,

1480
00:50:18,135 --> 00:50:19,974
four regular phos,

1481
00:50:19,975 --> 00:50:21,705
one boo paht pong curry,

1482
00:50:22,345 --> 00:50:23,405
and one rice with pork.

1483
00:50:24,075 --> 00:50:26,915
Kang Full and I often drink here in the daytime.

1484
00:50:27,445 --> 00:50:28,445
- Here?
- Yes.

1485
00:50:28,446 --> 00:50:30,484
And do you want beer?

1486
00:50:30,485 --> 00:50:31,485
(Shaking his head)

1487
00:50:32,815 --> 00:50:34,055
We have to play a game soon.

1488
00:50:35,055 --> 00:50:36,154
I have to stay focused.

1489
00:50:36,155 --> 00:50:37,584
- We can't drink now.
- This isn't the time.

1490
00:50:37,585 --> 00:50:38,655
I feel great about it.

1491
00:50:38,795 --> 00:50:40,395
I feel like we can succeed in the second one.

1492
00:50:40,925 --> 00:50:42,524
We at least deserve to eat.

1493
00:50:42,525 --> 00:50:44,395
- We do.
- All thanks to Jeong Min.

1494
00:50:44,695 --> 00:50:45,735
- Absolutely.
- No, it's not.

1495
00:50:45,895 --> 00:50:46,895
He's right.

1496
00:50:47,195 --> 00:50:49,664
Do you have daughters or sons?

1497
00:50:49,665 --> 00:50:50,765
Two sons.

1498
00:50:51,505 --> 00:50:53,334
It must be hectic when they get playful.

1499
00:50:53,335 --> 00:50:56,575
I went to Latvia to film the show recently.

1500
00:50:57,305 --> 00:51:00,045
And once I go abroad...

1501
00:51:00,545 --> 00:51:01,744
You don't come back for a long time.

1502
00:51:01,745 --> 00:51:03,215
I heard they cried.

1503
00:51:03,585 --> 00:51:04,645
Did they cry?

1504
00:51:04,745 --> 00:51:07,154
- They said they missed me.
- Naturally.

1505
00:51:07,155 --> 00:51:08,785
- You can videocall them.
- I did.

1506
00:51:09,355 --> 00:51:10,854
Even if you do, it's a bit...

1507
00:51:10,855 --> 00:51:12,895
But after a week or ten days,

1508
00:51:13,195 --> 00:51:15,295
we were on a video call,

1509
00:51:15,625 --> 00:51:17,925
and he said to his brother, "You take it."

1510
00:51:18,395 --> 00:51:19,835
- They don't want to?
- Neither.

1511
00:51:20,335 --> 00:51:22,604
- That's how sons are.
- Right.

1512
00:51:22,605 --> 00:51:23,805
Indeed.

1513
00:51:24,265 --> 00:51:26,305
- It's a hassle now.
- In like two weeks,

1514
00:51:26,635 --> 00:51:27,905
they weren't so glad.

1515
00:51:28,675 --> 00:51:30,345
How are things between you and your brother, In Sung?

1516
00:51:30,705 --> 00:51:33,414
- Well, we're brothers, - Right.

1517
00:51:33,415 --> 00:51:35,585
- so we're not exactly affectionate.
- Yes.

1518
00:51:35,915 --> 00:51:37,485
- Still...
- Yes.

1519
00:51:37,845 --> 00:51:39,054
- Jeong Min, do you have a brother?
- A younger sister.

1520
00:51:39,055 --> 00:51:40,315
- A younger sister?
- A younger sister?

1521
00:51:40,555 --> 00:51:41,954
How are things between you and her?

1522
00:51:41,955 --> 00:51:42,955
We're on bad terms.

1523
00:51:43,555 --> 00:51:44,725
- Bad terms?
- Well, not exactly bad.

1524
00:51:45,525 --> 00:51:47,125
- You're not that affectionate.
- Right.

1525
00:51:47,655 --> 00:51:48,694
(Trying to save it after answering fast)

1526
00:51:48,695 --> 00:51:49,895
- We're not on bad terms.
- "We're on bad terms."

1527
00:51:51,825 --> 00:51:53,194
You also have a nephew, right?

1528
00:51:53,195 --> 00:51:55,235
Yes. Three.

1529
00:51:55,435 --> 00:51:56,465
Three?

1530
00:51:56,805 --> 00:51:58,365
I wish I had a nephew.

1531
00:51:58,435 --> 00:52:01,634
But I'm kind of glad that I have nephews.

1532
00:52:01,635 --> 00:52:02,675
Because...

1533
00:52:02,945 --> 00:52:05,544
now that they're 3 or 4 years old,

1534
00:52:05,545 --> 00:52:08,074
they're cute, so I try to play with them.

1535
00:52:08,075 --> 00:52:09,644
But once they throw a tantrum...

1536
00:52:09,645 --> 00:52:12,115
- Oh, right.
- and start lying on the floor,

1537
00:52:12,185 --> 00:52:13,815
I just go home.

1538
00:52:15,625 --> 00:52:16,684
Parents are amazing.

1539
00:52:16,685 --> 00:52:17,885
I just go home.

1540
00:52:19,125 --> 00:52:20,594
(The uncle nonchalantly runs home.)

1541
00:52:20,595 --> 00:52:22,194
- I can find them cute, - Right.

1542
00:52:22,195 --> 00:52:24,225
but I can't deal with that.

1543
00:52:24,395 --> 00:52:26,034
The good part about having a nephew is...

1544
00:52:26,035 --> 00:52:27,594
- that you can go home.
- Yes, when they throw tantrums.

1545
00:52:27,595 --> 00:52:28,665
(You can run away when they throw a tantrum.)

1546
00:52:29,065 --> 00:52:30,205
Thank you for the food.

1547
00:52:30,565 --> 00:52:31,935
- It looks good.
- Eat up.

1548
00:52:34,405 --> 00:52:35,475
You can tell right away.

1549
00:52:35,575 --> 00:52:37,045
It already smells delicious.

1550
00:52:37,205 --> 00:52:38,274
That looks good.

1551
00:52:38,275 --> 00:52:39,645
It brings me back to Thailand.

1552
00:52:40,475 --> 00:52:42,185
I love these. Soft crabs.

1553
00:52:42,385 --> 00:52:43,915
This one also looks good.

1554
00:52:45,045 --> 00:52:47,155
(A big bite)

1555
00:52:47,385 --> 00:52:49,354
- I hope you like it.
- This is good.

1556
00:52:49,355 --> 00:52:50,355
Right?

1557
00:52:51,655 --> 00:52:53,825
(Jeong Min tries the soup first.)

1558
00:52:53,895 --> 00:52:56,165
- Man, that's rich.
- This is...

1559
00:52:56,225 --> 00:52:57,394
- It's great.
- It's good, right?

1560
00:52:57,395 --> 00:52:58,665
Yes. The soup is amazing.

1561
00:53:00,465 --> 00:53:01,465
It's great.

1562
00:53:03,735 --> 00:53:05,464
(Hae Joon also slurps the noodles.)

1563
00:53:05,465 --> 00:53:06,805
That's good.

1564
00:53:07,205 --> 00:53:08,235
It's tasty.

1565
00:53:09,205 --> 00:53:10,945
- You must like coriander.
- I do.

1566
00:53:11,275 --> 00:53:14,115
There's a scent you expect when eating Southeast Asian food.

1567
00:53:14,545 --> 00:53:16,484
You add coriander to Yukgaejang cup noodles,

1568
00:53:16,485 --> 00:53:17,684
and it tastes like tom yum kung.

1569
00:53:17,685 --> 00:53:19,055
- Yukgaejang?
- I bet it does.

1570
00:53:19,685 --> 00:53:20,955
I never thought of that.

1571
00:53:21,885 --> 00:53:23,225
I do like coriander.

1572
00:53:23,655 --> 00:53:26,655
Oh, Yukgaejang. In spicy soup?

1573
00:53:27,695 --> 00:53:30,195
I love soft crab.

1574
00:53:31,465 --> 00:53:33,634
- I've never tried that.
- Do you eat the shell too?

1575
00:53:33,635 --> 00:53:34,995
Yes. The whole thing.

1576
00:53:36,905 --> 00:53:38,135
Or you can eat it with rice.

1577
00:53:38,165 --> 00:53:39,474
(Moaning)

1578
00:53:39,475 --> 00:53:40,505
- It's good.
- Good.

1579
00:53:41,105 --> 00:53:42,475
The curry is so good.

1580
00:53:42,605 --> 00:53:44,305
Yeon Seok knows a lot of popular restaurants.

1581
00:53:44,805 --> 00:53:47,545
But Jae Suk doesn't like waiting in line.

1582
00:53:48,345 --> 00:53:50,244
The three of us were about to go to a convenience store.

1583
00:53:50,245 --> 00:53:51,315
Really?

1584
00:53:51,815 --> 00:53:52,955
We're similar.

1585
00:53:53,915 --> 00:53:56,085
- It's good that we waited.
- Right.

1586
00:53:58,285 --> 00:54:01,654
(The three guys who can eat anything enjoy the food.)

1587
00:54:01,655 --> 00:54:02,665
That's good.

1588
00:54:03,525 --> 00:54:04,864
I gulped it down.

1589
00:54:04,865 --> 00:54:06,735
We need to play a game to decide who pays.

1590
00:54:06,795 --> 00:54:07,964
We need to make it clear.

1591
00:54:07,965 --> 00:54:09,604
(Deciding who pays)

1592
00:54:09,605 --> 00:54:10,605
How about this?

1593
00:54:11,105 --> 00:54:13,135
We put a note in one of the cups,

1594
00:54:13,475 --> 00:54:14,675
and we open one each.

1595
00:54:14,875 --> 00:54:15,875
If you don't have a note, you leave.

1596
00:54:15,876 --> 00:54:17,904
- We can put them upside down.
- Exactly.

1597
00:54:17,905 --> 00:54:19,315
- Five cups.
- Five cups.

1598
00:54:19,975 --> 00:54:21,644
Do we have something to mark it?

1599
00:54:21,645 --> 00:54:24,084
We'll use our cups.

1600
00:54:24,085 --> 00:54:25,145
(Time for a dopamine rush)

1601
00:54:25,955 --> 00:54:26,955
All right.

1602
00:54:27,685 --> 00:54:28,715
Put them here.

1603
00:54:28,815 --> 00:54:30,455
Would you like a piece of coriander in one of the cups?

1604
00:54:30,585 --> 00:54:31,924
- Yes.
- Okay.

1605
00:54:31,925 --> 00:54:32,994
We'll put it in.

1606
00:54:32,995 --> 00:54:34,924
- The loser has to eat it.
- This cup is...

1607
00:54:34,925 --> 00:54:37,295
The loser has to eat the coriander.

1608
00:54:37,365 --> 00:54:38,365
(Pondering)

1609
00:54:38,366 --> 00:54:39,595
Including coffee?

1610
00:54:39,895 --> 00:54:41,264
- Even coffee?
- In one go.

1611
00:54:41,265 --> 00:54:42,265
Yes.

1612
00:54:43,365 --> 00:54:45,934
Should we wait in our rooms?

1613
00:54:45,935 --> 00:54:47,434
- Let's wait there.
- Yes.

1614
00:54:47,435 --> 00:54:48,574
We'll come out one at a time.

1615
00:54:48,575 --> 00:54:50,745
Yes, we'll come out one at a time and pick one.

1616
00:54:51,145 --> 00:54:52,715
- You can leave when you win.
- Okay.

1617
00:54:53,315 --> 00:54:55,145
- If it's empty, we just leave?
- Yes.

1618
00:54:55,885 --> 00:54:56,944
You can just step out.

1619
00:54:56,945 --> 00:54:58,914
(They all go to the other room.)

1620
00:54:58,915 --> 00:55:00,015
I'll get my jacket first.

1621
00:55:00,455 --> 00:55:01,755
It's what I used to do back in high school.

1622
00:55:01,785 --> 00:55:02,785
The order.

1623
00:55:03,025 --> 00:55:04,455
- Rock, paper, scissors.
- Rock, paper, scissors.

1624
00:55:04,725 --> 00:55:06,524
- Rock, paper, scissors.
- Rock, paper, scissors.

1625
00:55:06,525 --> 00:55:07,554
(Hae Joon and Yeon Seok lose.)

1626
00:55:07,555 --> 00:55:09,525
- Rock, paper, scissors.
- Does the order matter, though?

1627
00:55:09,665 --> 00:55:10,824
- Okay.
- Go.

1628
00:55:10,825 --> 00:55:12,594
Wait. That doesn't seem so bad.

1629
00:55:12,595 --> 00:55:14,595
No. They might not lose until it gets to you.

1630
00:55:15,165 --> 00:55:16,304
(Only one cup holds coriander.)

1631
00:55:16,305 --> 00:55:18,834
- That's true.
- I'm likely to win.

1632
00:55:18,835 --> 00:55:20,075
He might pick it right away.

1633
00:55:21,135 --> 00:55:24,775
(He might pick it right away.)

1634
00:55:26,075 --> 00:55:27,544
(In Sung passes.)

1635
00:55:27,545 --> 00:55:28,575
Okay.

1636
00:55:28,875 --> 00:55:30,384
- Let's see.
- He didn't get it.

1637
00:55:30,385 --> 00:55:31,815
- No?
- No.

1638
00:55:31,945 --> 00:55:34,015
- Thanks for the food.
- Oh, no.

1639
00:55:34,955 --> 00:55:36,954
- This is...
- You can leave.

1640
00:55:36,955 --> 00:55:38,084
Number two, Jeong Min.

1641
00:55:38,085 --> 00:55:39,124
(The next person carefully comes out.)

1642
00:55:39,125 --> 00:55:40,695
You can leave.

1643
00:55:43,865 --> 00:55:45,495
That's the one.

1644
00:55:50,905 --> 00:55:52,505
(Screaming)

1645
00:55:53,235 --> 00:55:55,745
(We have a loser!)

1646
00:55:56,005 --> 00:55:57,704
(Jeong Min will pay for food and coffee.)

1647
00:55:57,705 --> 00:55:59,115
But he's the youngest.

1648
00:56:00,315 --> 00:56:03,185
You're the king of games today.

1649
00:56:03,345 --> 00:56:04,345
(The king of games puts his head down.)

1650
00:56:04,346 --> 00:56:05,545
Goodness.

1651
00:56:05,645 --> 00:56:07,814
Jeong Min, thanks for paying.

1652
00:56:07,815 --> 00:56:09,854
- Jeong Min.
- Jeong Min.

1653
00:56:09,855 --> 00:56:10,855
You don't have to eat the coriander.

1654
00:56:10,856 --> 00:56:12,325
- Great, Jeong Min.
- Man.

1655
00:56:12,425 --> 00:56:13,795
He's doing great.

1656
00:56:13,995 --> 00:56:15,524
- Today, Jeong Min is...
- You're the king of games.

1657
00:56:15,525 --> 00:56:16,624
He's a master.

1658
00:56:16,625 --> 00:56:18,024
That's impressive.

1659
00:56:18,025 --> 00:56:19,995
- The king. You're the best.
- Thanks for paying.

1660
00:56:20,395 --> 00:56:21,435
He gets all the spotlight.

1661
00:56:21,795 --> 00:56:23,434
- That's a large bill.
- Thank you.

1662
00:56:23,435 --> 00:56:25,435
- We'll come again.
- Thank you.

1663
00:56:25,605 --> 00:56:26,605
Goodness.

1664
00:56:26,705 --> 00:56:28,274
(The older ones leave with light steps.)

1665
00:56:28,275 --> 00:56:30,145
Getting free food isn't a crime.

1666
00:56:30,305 --> 00:56:31,305
Right.

1667
00:56:31,306 --> 00:56:33,845
You didn't even give me a chance to flip a cup.

1668
00:56:34,075 --> 00:56:35,315
You're the star today.

1669
00:56:35,815 --> 00:56:37,644
- You're the star.
- You're so greedy.

1670
00:56:37,645 --> 00:56:39,414
He is. He didn't even give us a chance.

1671
00:56:39,415 --> 00:56:40,914
- I always lose bets like this.
- Not even a chance.

1672
00:56:40,915 --> 00:56:42,884
- Thanks for the food, Mr. Park.
- Okay.

1673
00:56:42,885 --> 00:56:44,084
Let's get coffee.

1674
00:56:44,085 --> 00:56:45,285
- That way.
- Let's go.

1675
00:56:47,495 --> 00:56:49,795
(He can't help but laugh, thinking about buying coffee too.)

1676
00:56:49,895 --> 00:56:51,124
On the bus, Jeong Min said...

1677
00:56:51,125 --> 00:56:53,695
that he hated losing bets.

1678
00:56:54,535 --> 00:56:56,404
(Jeong Min's words came true.)

1679
00:56:56,405 --> 00:56:58,364
I actually hate it. It hurts my pride.

1680
00:56:58,365 --> 00:57:00,734
- Yes.
- He said he hated it!

1681
00:57:00,735 --> 00:57:02,645
He said that he hated losing the most.

1682
00:57:02,975 --> 00:57:04,145
And he ended up losing.

1683
00:57:04,775 --> 00:57:06,244
My body feels warm now.

1684
00:57:06,245 --> 00:57:08,915
- Is there a coffee shop you go to?
- It's down the road.

1685
00:57:10,915 --> 00:57:12,245
It got cold again.

1686
00:57:12,585 --> 00:57:13,655
Right?

1687
00:57:13,755 --> 00:57:14,914
I was thinking the same thing.

1688
00:57:14,915 --> 00:57:15,924
(Their temperature goes down upon leaving.)

1689
00:57:15,925 --> 00:57:17,155
- It was...
- I was almost feeling hot.

1690
00:57:18,385 --> 00:57:19,824
- You want my jacket?
- No.

1691
00:57:19,825 --> 00:57:20,895
"You want my jacket?"

1692
00:57:21,395 --> 00:57:23,025
You didn't sound like you meant it at all.

1693
00:57:23,765 --> 00:57:25,294
He didn't say, "I'll give you my jacket."

1694
00:57:25,295 --> 00:57:26,395
He said, "You want my jacket?"

1695
00:57:26,595 --> 00:57:28,135
(Embarrassed)

1696
00:57:28,895 --> 00:57:30,464
- Wait.
- Why is the sign so long?

1697
00:57:30,465 --> 00:57:32,705
- That's cool.
- "The Pierrot Is Free..."

1698
00:57:32,905 --> 00:57:34,074
"and Without Lust..."

1699
00:57:34,075 --> 00:57:35,804
- It says, "Greed."
- "Greed."

1700
00:57:35,805 --> 00:57:37,744
Did you say, "Lust?"

1701
00:57:37,745 --> 00:57:38,844
- Hey.
- "Lust?"

1702
00:57:38,845 --> 00:57:41,174
- It looks like "Lust!"
- It says, "Greed."

1703
00:57:41,175 --> 00:57:42,814
- Doesn't it say, "Lust?"
- No.

1704
00:57:42,815 --> 00:57:45,315
- It says, "Greed?"
- How did you misread that?

1705
00:57:45,785 --> 00:57:47,485
Goodness. This looks good.

1706
00:57:47,655 --> 00:57:49,114
Get a cup of coffee, guys.

1707
00:57:49,115 --> 00:57:50,555
We need coffee.

1708
00:57:50,755 --> 00:57:52,324
Jeong Min has to pay for these too?

1709
00:57:52,325 --> 00:57:53,955
- Yes.
- Gosh.

1710
00:57:54,495 --> 00:57:56,425
(He's already reading the menu.)

1711
00:57:56,465 --> 00:57:57,764
I'll have a latte.

1712
00:57:57,765 --> 00:57:59,595
- Mild latte.
- A latte sounds good.

1713
00:57:59,865 --> 00:58:01,735
One hot Americano.

1714
00:58:02,135 --> 00:58:03,465
I'll have a regular latte.

1715
00:58:03,665 --> 00:58:05,765
I'll have a single-origin coffee.

1716
00:58:06,135 --> 00:58:09,505
One Seongnae-dong Coffee, please.

1717
00:58:09,645 --> 00:58:10,905
Thanks, Jeong Min.

1718
00:58:12,045 --> 00:58:14,244
I feel a little bad, though.

1719
00:58:14,245 --> 00:58:16,715
- What? Come on.
- I feel bad.

1720
00:58:16,945 --> 00:58:18,344
He earns more than enough.

1721
00:58:18,345 --> 00:58:19,914
He's had a lot of commercial gigs lately.

1722
00:58:19,915 --> 00:58:21,214
- Right.
- Yes.

1723
00:58:21,215 --> 00:58:22,484
- For here?
- Yes.

1724
00:58:22,485 --> 00:58:23,724
Okay. All done.

1725
00:58:23,725 --> 00:58:24,925
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

1726
00:58:25,185 --> 00:58:26,954
Should we book the taxi for 40 or 50?

1727
00:58:26,955 --> 00:58:28,655
- For 40.
- For 40?

1728
00:58:28,955 --> 00:58:30,995
Do you actually book the taxi and everything?

1729
00:58:31,265 --> 00:58:32,265
Yes.

1730
00:58:32,765 --> 00:58:34,164
(Fascinated)

1731
00:58:34,165 --> 00:58:36,905
Yeon Seok should be paid more for his part-time job.

1732
00:58:38,035 --> 00:58:40,005
(One hand in his pocket)

1733
00:58:40,275 --> 00:58:41,574
(Staring)

1734
00:58:41,575 --> 00:58:43,574
You must be really sensitive to cold.

1735
00:58:43,575 --> 00:58:45,645
No.

1736
